The district South of A Street in Santa Rosa, California is called the SOFA district. Every year they have a sofa parade. Featuring actual sofas. 

{{< glightbox src="https://leo.fm/uploads/2024/img-2420.jpeg" alt="Auto-generated description: A lively mural on a long wall features various colorful characters, including a snowman, a person holding a torch, children playing, and animals parading."  title="Welcome to the Sofa District" >}}

{{< glightbox  src="https://leo.fm/uploads/2024/7eb6b33581.jpeg"  alt="Auto-generated description: A group of people in colorful outfits and wigs are parading with a decorated float featuring umbrellas and a large face cutout, with a rainbow flag." title="Ellen's sofa on parade" >}}

{{< glightbox  src="https://leo.fm/uploads/2024/8f558362d0.jpeg"  alt="Auto-generated description: People are standing on a street, some holding bubble machines while others walk, with a child running in the background."  title="Cloudy with a chance of bubbles" >}}

{{< glightbox  src="https://leo.fm/uploads/2024/836bf1f94c.jpeg"  alt="Auto-generated description: A person wearing a striped coat and black pants is walking outside holding a black and white striped umbrella."  title="Parasol" >}}

{{< glightbox  src="https://leo.fm/uploads/2024/352d3080be.jpeg" alt="70s disco bicycle rider"  title="Easy rider" >}}

The new M4 Pro Mac mini arrived today. (Buddha for scale.)

{{< glightbox src="https://leo.fm/uploads/2024/img-2445.jpeg" alt="The new mac mini in a stack with a blue buddha and the Mac Studio it's replacing" title="Bhudda for scale" >}}

It's so small and cute. And the internal drive is very very fast. 

{{< glightbox src="https://leo.fm/uploads/2024/screenshot-2024-11-11-at-11.57.49pm.png" alt="Blackmagic Disk Speed Test results showing 6647 MB/s write and 5397.2 read speeds" title="Blackmagic Speed Test results" >}}

Quiet, too.

